$120 there for her.

41:37.120 --> 41:40.081
- I don't, I don't
know what to say.

41:41.041 --> 41:42.500
God bless you.

41:42.584 --> 41:43.793
Thank you.

41:43.877 --> 41:44.896
- I'm gonna ring
these up in the back.

41:44.920 --> 41:45.920
- Alright.

41:59.851 --> 42:00.894
- We're closed.

42:02.354 --> 42:03.605
I said we're closed.

42:05.857 --> 42:06.942
- Hello, son.

42:11.404 --> 42:12.404
- What you want?

42:17.452 --> 42:19.329
- I missed you and
I wanted to see you.

42:20.205 --> 42:21.915
Your brother came by the house.

42:21.998 --> 42:24.417
- I'm not gonna ask
you again, alright?

42:24.501 --> 42:25.877
- Why are you so angry?

42:30.924 --> 42:31.967
- What can I do for you?

42:34.219 --> 42:37.013
- I was going through
some things the other day,

42:37.097 --> 42:39.432
and I came across this,
thought you should have it.

42:41.142 --> 42:42.142
- A bible?

42:43.728 --> 42:45.730
- I laughed so hard
when I used to catch you

42:45.814 --> 42:47.732
and Malcolm playing
at being the reverend.

42:49.609 --> 42:50.920
We were so sure you
were going to be the one

42:50.944 --> 42:53.196
to follow in his footsteps.

42:53.280 --> 42:54.280
You had,

42:55.991 --> 42:57.075
you have

42:59.035 --> 43:01.538
the calling all over you.

43:14.092 --> 43:16.594
Can I have a hug before I go?

43:23.560 --> 43:26.354
I love you and God loves you

43:27.772 --> 43:29.232
and it's time you came home.

43:31.359 --> 43:34.237
- Well that's,
that's funny because

43:36.781 --> 43:39.284
I keep having this dream
where I'm coming home.

43:43.079 --> 43:44.372
- God is working on you.

43:45.540 --> 43:46.583
I can feel it.

43:48.084 --> 43:50.420
And the moment you
stop fighting it,

43:50.503 --> 43:52.130
you'll see the
wonders of His love.

43:54.716 --> 43:57.260
- Well, thanks for
bringing me the bible.

43:58.470 --> 44:00.930
I really, I gotta close up shop.

44:01.014 --> 44:02.057
- Shhh.

44:03.308 --> 44:04.934
- Come on now.

44:20.909 --> 44:21.909
A bible?

44:27.040 --> 44:30.627
- Is that a new
suit and watch, Pastor?

44:32.128 --> 44:34.089
- Yeah, yeah.

44:34.172 --> 44:35.172
Yes it is.

44:35.882 --> 44:38.635
Well, you wear it well.

44:42.347 --> 44:45.016
I already put the new
member forms on your desk.

44:46.101 --> 44:49.104
- Okay, well thank you.

44:52.232 --> 44:53.650
- Yes.

44:53.983 --> 44:55.860
Looking good.

44:56.528 --> 44:57.612
Looking good.

45:04.619 --> 45:07.789
- Hey boss, you
know I was tripping earlier

45:07.872 --> 45:09.916
so I just wanna make sure...

45:09.999 --> 45:13.128
- Listen, listen, forget that.

45:13.211 --> 45:14.921
Did you spill my oil?

45:15.004 --> 45:16.089
- Your oil?

45:16.172 --> 45:18.216
- Yeah, it was almost full.

45:18.299 --> 45:19.342
It was up to here.

45:19.426 --> 45:21.261
Now, it's almost empty.

45:21.344 --> 45:23.221
- Yo, what's going
on with you, man?

45:23.304 --> 45:24.347
Some oil?

45:24.431 --> 45:25.640
What is this, man?

45:25.723 --> 45:26.784
We out here trying
to make money,

45:26.808 --> 45:27.600
you talking about some oil?

45:27.684 --> 45:29.269
- Look, I'm telling you, man.

45:29.352 --> 45:30.728
I know you spilled my oil.

45:30.812 --> 45:31.521
Alright?

45:31.604 --> 45:32.604
It was almost full.

45:33.731 --> 45:34.899
- You slippin'.

45:34.983 --> 45:36.001
Something's going on with you.

45:36.025 --> 45:37.305
You need to get your mind right.

45:37.360 --> 45:38.611
- I got my mind right.

45:38.695 --> 45:40.238
I'm not stupid.

45:40.321 --> 45:42.198
It was all full and
now it's all empty.

45:50.415 --> 45:51.708
- Get it together.

45:51.791 --> 45:53.391
These cats, they eat
your lunch, alright?

45:55.170 --> 45:57.172
- We gonna do this or what?

45:58.631 --> 45:59.631
- The bag.

46:07.307 --> 46:08.667
- What's up with your boy?

46:09.517 --> 46:11.144
- Relax, hey, O.

46:11.227 --> 46:12.562
O, come on.

46:12.645 --> 46:13.521
Hurry up.

46:13.605 --> 46:14.832
- Better get him outta there!

46:14.856 --> 46:16.056
- Hey, hey, you need to relax.

46:17.192 --> 46:17.859
You need to relax.

46:17.942 --> 46:19.194
- You need to relax.

46:19.277 --> 46:21.029
You need to pull him out.

46:21.112 --> 46:23.031
- Chill out, chill out, alright?

46:23.114 --> 46:24.157
We good.

46:25.658 --> 46:26.826
Silk, we good, alright?

46:26.910 --> 46:27.910
Look in the bag.

46:30.914 --> 46:31.914
Easy.

46:32.707 --> 46:34.292
- Thanks for coming to get me.

46:34.375 --> 46:37.712
I called Larry but he
didn't answer his phone, so.

46:40.882 --> 46:42.175
You know what?

46:42.258 --> 46:43.569
If it wasn't for my mama,
I wouldn't have even

46:43.593 --> 46:44.928
gone up there.

46:45.887 --> 46:47.347
What is this?

46:49.057 --> 46:50.058
What is this?

46:50.141 --> 46:51.059
- What was that?

46:51.142 --> 46:52.685
All you gotta do is
bring the bag out.

46:52.769 --> 46:53.829
- You gonna put this on me?

46:53.853 --> 46:54.646
You gonna put this on me?

46:54.729 --> 46:56.147
- Yeah, you got one job.

46:56.231 --> 46:58.066
- Let me tell you,
you know what?

46:58.149 --> 46:59.859
- you don't have to answer that.

46:59.943 --> 47:01.295
- What's that got
to do with anything?

47:01.319 --> 47:02.070
- What's this got?

47:02.153 --> 47:02.820
That's what I'm saying.

47:02.904 --> 47:03.655
- You got one job.

47:03.738 --> 47:04.405
Bring the money out.

47:04.489 --> 47:05.240
- What money?

47:05.323 --> 47:07.617
- What are you doing?

47:13.039 --> 47:15.166
Are you crazy?

47:15.250 --> 47:16.250
- I just...

47:18.878 --> 47:19.712
- Are you out of your mind?

47:19.796 --> 47:22.632
- You had a gun in a cemetery.

47:23.466 --> 47:25.051
You're not good.

47:25.134 --> 47:26.134
- I'm fine.

47:27.178 --> 47:28.721
Now I gotta go back
and get my gun.

47:42.277 --> 47:44.028
- I got you.

48:03.172 --> 48:05.842
- Caught the end
of your service.

48:05.925 --> 48:10.179
Made me wanna come up
there and get saved.

48:10.263 --> 48:12.515
- That so?

48:14.809 --> 48:16.686
How'd you even get in here?

48:22.066 --> 48:25.361
- I just need you to
cover me in prayers.

48:28.823 --> 48:30.700
- What is it, man?

48:30.783 --> 48:31.783
What'd you do?

48:33.202 --> 48:34.287
- Come on.

48:35.413 --> 48:37.582
Just, just cover me in prayers.

48:39.292 --> 48:42.795
I'm ready to go home.

48:42.879 --> 48:44.464
I'm ready to go home.

48:44.547 --> 48:45.840
- You are home.

48:45.923 --> 48:48.301
Stay with me, stay
with me, alright?

48:48.384 --> 48:49.384
Stay with me.

48:49.427 --> 48:50.738
- It's okay, I'm
ready to go home.

48:50.762 --> 48:51.822
- Pastor, what's going on?

48:51.846 --> 48:54.390
- Just call an ambulance now.

48:54.474 --> 48:56.476
- Ready to go home.

48:56.559 --> 48:57.870
- You're not
finished, you're not finished.

48:57.894 --> 48:59.312
Call an ambulance.

48:59.395 --> 49:02.398
- Yes, hi, we need an ambulance.

49:02.482 --> 49:03.816
- You're not finished.

49:03.900 --> 49:06.277
- At 1901 Crenshaw
Drive, back of the church.

49:09.155 --> 49:10.281
- Are they on the way?

49:10.365 --> 49:15.370
- Listen, listen just hurry up.

49:20.041 --> 49:23.169
Heavenly Father, Heavenly
Father we stand before You

49:23.252 --> 49:26.339
right now standing in
deep prayer of our Father.

49:26.422 --> 49:28.233
We don't know what brought
him in this condition,

49:28.257 --> 49:29.842
but we know that it's
not by coincidence

49:29.926 --> 49:31.427
that he is here at
Your house today.

49:31.511 --> 49:34.013
Heavenly Father, please, send
down Your angels of mercy

49:34.097 --> 49:36.516
upon us, send down Your
angels of mercy, please Lord.

49:36.599 --> 49:39.310
Cover him and watch him,
keep him dear Lord, shh...

49:40.436 --> 49:41.705
- Why y'all praying
for this boy?

49:41.729 --> 49:44.440
He ain't doing nothing
to sell no drugs.

49:44.524 --> 49:46.693
The bible says you
live by the sword

49:46.776 --> 49:50.321
so shall be written you reap
what you sow, by the sword.

49:50.405 --> 49:52.490
- Shh, Sister Jenkins, please.

49:54.158 --> 49:56.911
- You ain't got
to shush me twice.

49:56.994 --> 49:58.454
I'm calling the police.

49:59.414 --> 50:00.289
Heathen in here
selling drugs like

50:00.373 --> 50:02.250
it's a dad-gum grocery store.

50:07.213 --> 50:10.299
- So, what's the latest?

50:10.383 --> 50:13.136
- The doctors say he's not
responding to treatment.

50:13.219 --> 50:15.680
His blood pressure
just keeps dropping.

50:16.806 --> 50:17.890
- Have you gotten any rest?

50:17.974 --> 50:19.016
Have you eaten anything?

50:19.100 --> 50:20.351
- No, baby.

50:20.435 --> 50:24.313
- Ma, you still need to
take care of yourself.

50:24.397 --> 50:25.481
- I can't.

50:25.565 --> 50:28.359
I wanna be here
when he wakes up.

50:28.443 --> 50:31.696
- I promise you, if he
wakes up, I'll come get you.

50:31.779 --> 50:35.366
- Listen, I am
staying right here.

50:35.450 --> 50:38.202
- Mama, I don't want
to fight with you.

50:40.580 --> 50:41.580
Okay?

50:42.415 --> 50:45.668
If you get sick, you
won't be here for him.

50:49.005 --> 50:51.007
- You promise you'll
come and get me?

50:51.924 --> 50:52.924
- I promise.

50:59.182 --> 51:02.769
- Baby, you know why I
stay with your daddy?

51:04.437 --> 51:08.107
Because I wanna prove
to him that I love him

51:08.191 --> 51:09.358
more than he loves me.

51:09.442 --> 51:10.568
- But he hits you...

51:10.651 --> 51:13.279
- He loves me, that is all.

51:13.362 --> 51:17.158
I know without a shadow of
a doubt that he loves me.

51:18.451 --> 51:22.413
Whatever you think he is
doing to me, he saved me.

51:23.831 --> 51:27.585
Trust me, I am telling
you that he saved me.

51:30.046 --> 51:32.882
His is the only love
that I have ever known.

51:35.968 --> 51:37.762
I owe him everything.

51:49.857 --> 51:54.237
- Just do us all
a favor and die.

52:02.411 --> 52:03.496
- Here you go, Detective.

52:03.579 --> 52:05.498
Samuel Wiggins, but
they call him Silk.

52:05.581 --> 52:06.624
- Okay, thank you.

52:07.792 --> 52:09.502
- Pastor, I have your shirt.

52:10.545 --> 52:13.673
- So you have no idea
of how he got in here

52:13.756 --> 52:14.756
or who shot him?

52:16.008 --> 52:18.219
- No, officer, it's
like I told you...

52:18.302 --> 52:19.554
- Detective.

52:19.637 --> 52:22.139
- Excuse me, Detective,
it's like I told you

52:22.223 --> 52:24.559
when I came into
the office he was,

52:24.642 --> 52:26.060
he was there in that chair.

52:28.145 --> 52:30.690
- All due respect,
Pastor Stevens,

52:32.191 --> 52:34.694
but I'm just trying
to understand how

52:34.777 --> 52:36.487
one of the biggest

52:36.571 --> 52:38.406
drug dealers in the
city could get into

52:38.489 --> 52:40.658
your office without
anybody seeing him?

52:42.577 --> 52:46.080
Why would he come here instead
of going someplace else?

52:46.163 --> 52:49.083
- Well, maybe it's because
me and Silk grew up together.

52:49.166 --> 52:51.210
Practically from birth.

52:51.294 --> 52:53.004
That's no secret.

52:54.589 --> 52:56.382
- So, what's your
relationship now?

52:58.092 --> 52:59.218
- Pastor, we gotta go.

53:00.344 --> 53:02.179
- There's no, no relationship.

53:02.263 --> 53:04.724
I see him every once in a while.

53:07.560 --> 53:09.145
- And what do you talk about?

53:09.228 --> 53:10.605
- Pastor, we gotta go.

53:11.606 --> 53:12.607
I got your shirt, okay?

53:12.690 --> 53:15.568
- Same old song and
dance we've always done.

53:15.651 --> 53:17.612
I talk to him about
turning his life around

53:17.695 --> 53:20.573
and he always tells me he's
working for the other guy.

53:20.656 --> 53:23.659
- Has he ever talked to you
specifically about his business?

53:24.535 --> 53:26.078
- Why would he?

53:26.162 --> 53:29.165
- Naw, I mean, you said the
both of you go way back,

53:29.248 --> 53:30.833
so I figured well
maybe, you know,

53:30.917 --> 53:32.197
he'd wanna confide in his homie.

53:34.670 --> 53:36.547
You know, the good Reverend.

53:39.258 --> 53:42.219
- Listen, Detective.

53:42.303 --> 53:46.432
Now I know no one may
cry a river over Samuel,

53:46.515 --> 53:48.476
but what I see is someone
who's still trying

53:48.559 --> 53:51.520
to turn their life
around, that's what I see.

53:51.604 --> 53:53.689
And I understand you
have a job to do,

53:55.066 --> 53:57.401
but my focus here
is on a human being

53:57.485 --> 53:59.403
that's clinging to life.

53:59.487 --> 54:02.156
Alright, that's
what my focus is.

54:02.239 --> 54:04.075
So, unless we have
anything else here,

54:05.701 --> 54:08.162
can I get cleaned up
and get outta here?

54:08.245 --> 54:09.525
- Naw, I think we're about done.

54:10.331 --> 54:14.752
Yeah, I'm gonna ask
ya some more questions

54:14.835 --> 54:17.254
in a few days and
don't make any plans

54:17.338 --> 54:22.301
to take a trip anywhere until
we get this cleared up, okay?

54:24.470 --> 54:27.640
- Well, Detective, you'll
know where to find me.

54:28.557 --> 54:30.977
- Thank you, thank you, come on.

54:39.568 --> 54:43.823
- Paging Dr.
Bender, paging Dr. Bender.

54:56.502 --> 54:57.795
Are you the doctor?

54:57.878 --> 54:59.839
- Excuse me, are you
Mr. Wiggins' family?

54:59.922 --> 55:02.967
- Yes, he's my foster
brother and I'm his pastor.

55:03.050 --> 55:04.343
